A '''prayer walk''' is an activity that consists in walking and [[Prayer|praying]] at the same time. It's done not for the physical benefit but for the spiritual exercise, either publicly functioning also as a [[demonstration (people)|demonstration]] or rally (to let other people know the group is praying), or quietly in sight of the subject. For instance, a person or group may be praying for a town or city, and walk the streets of the city while praying, either out loud, or in silence.

